1
00:00:18,230 --> 00:00:21,320
Lin Hua, have another drink with me.

2
00:00:23,030 --> 00:00:24,000
Don't leave!

3
00:00:24,510 --> 00:00:26,510
Have some more.

4
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:28,160
Get over here.

5
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,030
Stop running!

6
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:30,800
You punk.

7
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:33,280
Where do you think you're going?

8
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,150
Get back here.

9
00:00:35,390 --> 00:00:36,720
Get back here right now!

10
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:38,880
Stop running! Stop!

11
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:42,640
-My leg! My leg!
-Are you running or not?

12
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,390
It'd serve you right if it broke!

13
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:46,450
Try running again.

14
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:47,340
Try running again.

15
00:00:47,340 --> 00:00:47,940
Stop!

16
00:00:48,030 --> 00:00:49,560
Why are you hitting Lin Hua?

17
00:00:50,110 --> 00:00:52,670
Thanks for helping me out yesterday.

18
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:55,840
Lin Hua, your foot will get better.

19
00:00:56,150 --> 00:00:58,030
Lu Ming and I will both be here for you.

20
00:00:58,030 --> 00:00:58,420
Yes.

21
00:00:59,470 --> 00:01:01,030
By the way,
there's a lot of homework today.

22
00:01:01,030 --> 00:01:02,240
Can you finish it?

23
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:03,110
I can.

24
00:01:03,110 --> 00:01:04,129
Me too!

25
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,379
Me too!

26
00:01:05,710 --> 00:01:06,760
You're the one who can't finish it.

27
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:08,230
You won't finish.

28
00:01:08,230 --> 00:01:09,000
You won't finish.

29
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,860
You miswrote the character biao!

30
00:01:13,039 --> 00:01:14,340
Damn cripple.

31
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:15,640
Damn cripple.

32
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:19,840
Cripple, cripple, cripple.

33
00:01:26,070 --> 00:01:27,000
Ouch! Ouch!

34
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:27,840
It hurts.

35
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:29,870
Gentle. Be gentle!

36
00:01:29,870 --> 00:01:30,840
Now you're afraid of pain?

37
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,770
Where's that fighting spirit now?

38
00:01:34,479 --> 00:01:35,330
Be gentle.

39
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:36,280
I can't take it anymore!

40
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,000
Maybe...

41
00:01:38,350 --> 00:01:40,210
We shouldn't be friends anymore.

42
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,090
Lin Hua.

43
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:46,000
Did you get hit in the head
during the fight?

44
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,340
Yeah, why are you talking nonsense?

45
00:01:50,509 --> 00:01:52,039
I'm lame now.

46
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:55,560
I can't play with you two.

47
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,479
I'll just be a burden wherever you go.

48
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:02,100
I don't wanna be like this!

49
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,150
Bullshit!

50
00:02:03,430 --> 00:02:05,070
We are friends forever.

51
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:06,800
Nothing will ever change that.

52
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,590
Even if you're crippled

53
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:11,320
or even paralyzed,
I'll carry you wherever we go!

54
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,650
Right, we're friends forever.

55
00:02:14,190 --> 00:02:14,850
Lin Hua.

56
00:02:15,030 --> 00:02:17,800
If your mom is on night shift again,

57
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,120
we'll go keep you company.

58
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,980
We'll see if Old Lin
dares to lay a finger on you then!

59
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,560
I stole this from my grandpa's house.

60
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,290
It's for you.

61
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:28,560
This one is for you.

62
00:02:30,470 --> 00:02:31,930
And this one is for myself.

63
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:33,150
From now on, if any of us

64
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:34,870
is alone and in danger,

65
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:36,200
just blow this whistle.

66
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,280
The rest of us will come
as soon as we hear it!

67
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,700
Pretty smart, huh?

68
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:42,440
You're actually pretty smart.

69
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,360
Thank you,

70
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:44,910
Lu Ming.

71
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:46,820
Try blowing it!

72
00:02:56,329 --> 00:03:03,540
[Be friends forever:
Lu Ming, Xia Xue, Lin Hua]

73
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:39,970
[THE GUILTY]

74
00:04:40,170 --> 00:04:45,480
[Episode 11]

75
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,040
Hello. We're the police.

76
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:47,680
Do you remember the person

77
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,360
who was sitting at that table

78
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,430
between 5:30 and 6:30

79
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:51,800
yesterday?

80
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:53,040
Yes.

81
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:54,680
I definitely do!

82
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,659
Yesterday afternoon,

83
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:59,120
this guy walked into my shop
out of nowhere.

84
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,210
He was sitting right there.

85
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,710
He asked me to hand over Hou Shanshan.

86
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,750
But the kid's name is Ma Shanshan.

87
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,930
She's my old friend's granddaughter.

88
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:12,920
After Ma Derong was released,

89
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,890
he asked me

90
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:15,870
to help him find a place

91
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:17,990
to live with his granddaughter.

92
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,620
I busted my hump to find a spot for him.

93
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:25,160
So the old friend you mentioned is...

94
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:25,870
Ma Derong?

95
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:27,750
Yes.

96
00:05:29,710 --> 00:05:31,320
Where is the place you found for him?

97
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,650
This one is unoccupied.

98
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:36,600
What about these two?

99
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,950
They are unoccupied too. Nobody's here.

100
00:05:37,950 --> 00:05:39,550
This one is also unoccupied.

101
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:44,830
This is occupied.

102
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:52,920
Hello, routine check.

103
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,050
Please show your ID.

104
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,090
This room is occupied, too.

105
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:18,920
Who is it?

106
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:19,560
Routine check.

107
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,690
Please show your ID.

108
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,000
Do you live alone?

109
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:24,430
Yes.

110
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,170
She lives alone.

111
00:06:26,830 --> 00:06:27,310
Okay.

112
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:28,190
Give it back to her.

113
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:29,950
Thank you for your cooperation.

114
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:30,750
Open the door.

115
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:53,159
[Police]

116
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:54,360
Captain Qin.

117
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,270
We searched Ma Derong's place.
No one's there.

118
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:57,330
We've searched the whole village,

119
00:06:57,330 --> 00:06:58,360
but found nothing.

120
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,560
Issue an arrest warrant.

121
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,820
Search the whole city.

122
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,730
-Yes, Madam.
-Yes, Madam.

123
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:01,830
[Police]

124
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:02,360
Let's go.

125
00:07:04,850 --> 00:07:11,080
[Police]

126
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:20,970
Captain Qin,

127
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,630
there's something I don't understand.

128
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:24,690
Why aren't we interrogating Lu Ming?

129
00:07:24,830 --> 00:07:27,390
There might be a secret
between him and Ma Derong.

130
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:29,000
We're playing the long game
to catch the big fish.

131
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,240
What if he tries to run?

132
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:30,970
No ifs.

133
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,040
He has no other choice.

134
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,570
Only by trusting the police

135
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:36,920
can he find the truth he seeks.

136
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:46,870
Is your head okay?

137
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:49,530
I'm fine.

138
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:52,040
It's a relief the kid's back safe.

139
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:54,950
It's all my fault.

140
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,400
I lost track of Ma Derong.

141
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,480
Why didn't he just kill me?

142
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,440
I'm starting to think

143
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:10,220
he might have another motive.

144
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:13,920
Another motive?

145
00:08:14,780 --> 00:08:15,640
Think about it.

146
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:17,920
We all thought Ma Derong

147
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,320
kidnapped Hou Shanshan.

148
00:08:20,230 --> 00:08:21,430
But to save Shanshan,

149
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:23,060
he killed Wang Bingkun.

150
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,760
That means it wasn't him
who kidnapped her.

151
00:08:30,070 --> 00:08:31,800
What if the kidnapping

152
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,909
was targeting Ma Derong all along?

153
00:08:34,789 --> 00:08:36,320
We never received any calls
from the kidnappers

154
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,380
or ransom demands.

155
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,570
It means the kidnapper didn't want money.

156
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:45,270
Uncle San,

157
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,330
what's so urgent?

158
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,840
After Shanshan was rescued,

159
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:57,000
Ma Derong made a new move.

160
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:58,950
I got word

161
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:01,360
that he started looking into

162
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:03,120
the shipyard explosion case.

163
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,650
Uncle San told me

164
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,320
after Ma Derong was released,

165
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:11,780
he started to investigate
the explosion case of the shipyard.

166
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:14,480
The explosion of the shipyard?

167
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:17,710
It wasn't an accident?

168
00:09:21,810 --> 00:09:23,020
Ma Ke!

169
00:09:25,460 --> 00:09:27,710
[Ma Ke]

170
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:31,510
Could it be related to
that unidentified body?

171
00:09:31,510 --> 00:09:33,120
It's been so many years,

172
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,850
and no family has ever shown up.

173
00:09:36,870 --> 00:09:38,630
Ma Derong is investigating the explosion,

174
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:40,760
and his granddaughter was kidnapped.

175
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,640
Could there be a link

176
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:45,240
between these two cases?

177
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,300
[Police]

178
00:10:08,790 --> 00:10:09,390
Boss,

179
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,850
you didn't come home all night?

180
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,120
The kid has been found.

181
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:23,400
The arrest warrant for Ma Derong
has been issued.

182
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,390
[Wang Bingkun]

183
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,390
He won't get away.

184
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:31,630
Wang Bingkun

185
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:33,740
was a key suspect
in Hou Shanshan's kidnapping.

186
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:34,670
I don't know him.

187
00:10:34,790 --> 00:10:35,630
He owed us money!

188
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:36,390
I collected a debt.

189
00:10:36,390 --> 00:10:37,720
Ma Derong is the prime suspect

190
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,270
in Wang Bingkun's murder.

191
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:40,320
But Grandpa isn't a bad person.

192
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:44,020
But I think there's something weird

193
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,610
about this kidnapping.

194
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,880
The child was kidnapped,

195
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,890
but no one asked for ransom.

196
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:53,000
So, what's the real reason

197
00:10:55,870 --> 00:10:57,200
behind kidnapping her?

198
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,720
You're right.

199
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,980
We've been thinking about this for days,

200
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,900
but we can't figure it out.

201
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,640
Ma Ke is Shanshan's biological father.

202
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,360
We got beaten up this bad.

203
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,460
How can we settle this  privately?

204
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,580
Ren Yi.

205
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:30,080
Ma Ke had a subordinate back then
named Li Dong.

206
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,510
Go find him.

207
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:32,750
Bring him in for a chat

208
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:35,000
and see if he knows anything about this.

209
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:35,960
Got it.

210
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,950
Eat something and get some sleep.

211
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:38,360
Okay.

212
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,570
Let's dig in.

213
00:11:52,870 --> 00:11:54,070
Have something warm.

214
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:56,600
Mom.

215
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:59,280
These are knee pads.

216
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:00,670
Put them on in winter.

217
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:01,390
[Knee Pads]

218
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:03,190
That way, your knees won't hurt.

219
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:06,190
And this plaster is for your back.

220
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:08,390
I asked a friend who's a sailor

221
00:12:08,390 --> 00:12:10,080
to bring it back from abroad.

222
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:11,630
Give it a try.

223
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:13,240
If it doesn't work and it still hurts,

224
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,200
go to the hospital right away.

225
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,460
Don't let it get worse.

226
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:18,840
Son.

227
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,120
I'm fine.

228
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:22,410
Why did you spend so much money?

229
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,050
Better safe than sorry.

230
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:25,670
Alright.

231
00:12:25,670 --> 00:12:26,530
Thanks, my son.

232
00:12:30,510 --> 00:12:31,440
Where is Old Lin?

233
00:12:31,570 --> 00:12:32,600
He left this morning.

234
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,480
Probably off playing mahjong somewhere.

235
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,240
Ignore him.

236
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:36,840
Have more meat.

237
00:12:39,510 --> 00:12:39,960
Mom.

238
00:12:40,630 --> 00:12:41,600
Take this.

239
00:12:42,390 --> 00:12:43,790
The PIN is your birthday.

240
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:44,750
Don't let Old Lin know it.

241
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:45,950
Hurry and put it away.

242
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:47,600
Son.

243
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:49,000
I can't take

244
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:49,840
the money.

245
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,200
It's not easy for you
to make money out there.

246
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,130
I've got enough.

247
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,440
I have more.

248
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,150
Mom, listen to me.

249
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,240
If you're willing,

250
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,440
take this money

251
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:05,150
so you don't have to
put up with his nonsense anymore.

252
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:05,600
Okay?

253
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,000
Son,

254
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,720
I really appreciate it.

255
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:17,680
Alright.

256
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:20,240
I'll keep and save it for you.

257
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,240
I won't spend it.

258
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:04,750
Don't run!

259
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:05,360
Stop!

260
00:14:10,630 --> 00:14:11,360
Stop!

261
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:18,410
[Sancheng Financial Services]

262
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:20,390
Chang.

263
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:21,550
Did you find Ma Derong?

264
00:14:21,550 --> 00:14:22,840
No.

265
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:24,480
Ming.

266
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,630
But I think this time,

267
00:14:25,630 --> 00:14:27,840
he might really try to sneak
out of the country by smuggling.

268
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:28,440
Keep looking for him.

269
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:29,840
That's what we're doing!

270
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,200
We're searching the docks,

271
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,750
Hongfa Auto Parts,

272
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,000
and Zhongmei Hotel.

273
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,790
Just keep searching them repeatedly,
I guess.

274
00:14:37,790 --> 00:14:38,250
I'm off.

275
00:14:42,910 --> 00:14:43,440
Lin Hua.

276
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:45,030
I still don't feel at ease.

277
00:14:45,030 --> 00:14:46,480
Go keep an eye
on the police station entrance,

278
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,480
and see if Ma Derong

279
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,270
will send someone

280
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:50,270
to deliver the DV tape to the police.

281
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:03,510
[Police]

282
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:08,100
[Police]

283
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,360
Don't kill me!

284
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:12,320
Don't kill me! I won't go!

285
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,200
I won't go!

286
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:14,720
Don't kill me!

287
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,270
I-I-I was wrong!

288
00:15:16,270 --> 00:15:17,000
I won't...

289
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,390
I won't do it again.

290
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:19,540
